### Interactive Mode — Gateway WS Method Examples
### These are JSON-RPC frames sent over the gateway WebSocket (ws://127.0.0.1:19100)

### Start interactive mode with default inputs
# WS ws://127.0.0.1:19100
# {"type":"request","id":"1","method":"interactive.start","params":{"agentId":"default"}}

### Start with specific inputs
# {"type":"request","id":"2","method":"interactive.start","params":{"agentId":"default","inputs":["mic","camera","screen"]}}

### Stop interactive mode
# {"type":"request","id":"3","method":"interactive.stop","params":{}}

### Enable camera and screen
# {"type":"request","id":"4","method":"interactive.enable","params":{"inputs":["camera","screen"]}}

### Disable camera
# {"type":"request","id":"5","method":"interactive.disable","params":{"inputs":["camera"]}}

### Get session status
# {"type":"request","id":"6","method":"interactive.status","params":{}}

### Get resolved config
# {"type":"request","id":"7","method":"interactive.configure","params":{}}

### --- cURL equivalents (HTTP hooks, if exposed) ---

# Start interactive (slash command via chat.send)
POST http://127.0.0.1:19100/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv ONI_GATEWAY_TOKEN}}

{
  "model": "default",
  "messages": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "/interactive"}
  ]
}

###

# Enable camera + screen (slash command via chat.send)
POST http://127.0.0.1:19100/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv ONI_GATEWAY_TOKEN}}

{
  "model": "default",
  "messages": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "/interactive enable camera,screen"}
  ]
}

###

# Check status (slash command via chat.send)
POST http://127.0.0.1:19100/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv ONI_GATEWAY_TOKEN}}

{
  "model": "default",
  "messages": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "/interactive status"}
  ]
}

###

# Exit interactive (slash command via chat.send)
POST http://127.0.0.1:19100/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv ONI_GATEWAY_TOKEN}}

{
  "model": "default",
  "messages": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "/exit interactive"}
  ]
}
